questions.question:
Let L be a regular language. Consider the constructions on L below:
I.   repeat(L) = {ww | w in L}
II.  prefix(L) = {u | uw in L for some w in Sigma*}
III. suffix(L) = {v | uv in L for some u in Sigma*}
IV.  half(L) = {u | uw in L, |u| = |w|}

Which of the constructions could lead to a non-regular language?
A. Both I and IV
B. Only I
C. Only IV
D. Both II and III

Let L be a regular language. Consider the constructions on L below:
I.   repeat(L) = {ww | w in L}
II.  prefix(L) = {u | uw in L for some w in Sigma*}
III. suffix(L) = {v | uv in L for some u in Sigma*}
IV.  half(L) = {u | uw in L, |u| = |w|}

(This is the follow-up to the previous question.) Which choice of L is best suited to support your answer that both I and IV can lead to a non-regular language?

A. L = (a+b)*
B. L = {a^(2n) | n >= 0}
C. (ab)^+
D. {a^n b^n | n >= 0}
